author: Calvin Coolidge
message: We cannot do everything at once, but we can do something at once.
title: Thought of the day

author: Abraham Lincoln
message: You have to do your own growing no matter how tall your grandfather was.
title: Thought of the day

message: Invent your world. Surround yourself with people, color, sounds, and work that nourish you.
title: Thought of the day

author: General Douglas MacArthur
message: It is fatal to enter any war without the will to win it.
title: Thought of the day
